cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on analyzing and predicting sentence deletion in text simplification, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses a classification model to predict sentence deletion, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of discourse level factors, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
